  "original_title": "35 \u0bb5\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b86\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Consent in trade unions required to appoint graduates above 35 years as teachers - Education Minister",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Education Minister Sushil Premajayantha said that if the unions agree, the 24,000 graduates currently working in education offices can also be incorporated as teachers.",
        "He said this while replying to a question raised by opposition party member Pudhika Pathirana during oral question time in Parliament on Monday (4).",
        "Age issues are seen in appointing graduates as teachers. They must be under 35 years of age to be appointed as teachers in government service.",
        "Most of the above graduates who have expressed interest in teaching services are found to be above 35 years of age.",
        "Because according to Yap, graduates should not exceed 35 years of age if they are to join the teaching profession. At this stage, it is necessary to negotiate with the trade unions.",
        "If such negotiations are conducted and their agreement is obtained, steps can be taken to appoint the above graduates as teachers.",
        "When so appointed their allowance will also be increased by a further Rs.6700. They are currently working as office workers.",
        "It takes the decision of the trade unions to integrate them into the teaching service. He said that graduates can be recruited into government service up to the age of 45."
      ],
